---
import Layout from "@halleyfante/documentation/Layout";
import PixCode from "../components/PixCode.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Colors"
  description="Hex color literals and named color palettes in Pix"
  current="colors"
>
  <p>
    Colors in Pix are specified as hexadecimal literals or as references to
    named colors defined in a <code>color</code> block.
  </p>

  <h2>Hex colors</h2>
  <p>
    A hex color starts with <code>#</code> followed by 3, 6, or 8 hexadecimal
    digits. The digits are case-insensitive.
  </p>

  <h3>3-digit format</h3>
  <p>
    Each digit is expanded by repeating it. <code>#E40</code> becomes
    <code>#EE4400</code>. Alpha defaults to fully opaque.
  </p>
  <PixCode code={`#E40   // orange
#FFF   // white
#000   // black`} />

  <h3>6-digit format</h3>
  <p>
    Standard RGB hex: <code>#RRGGBB</code>. Each pair represents red, green, or
    blue in the range 0 to 255. Alpha defaults to fully opaque.
  </p>
  <PixCode code={`#e84a00   // accent orange
#e8ddd0   // warm beige
#2a1208   // dark brown
#b0a090   // muted tan`} />

  <h3>8-digit format</h3>
  <p>
    RGB with alpha: <code>#RRGGBBAA</code>. The last two digits set opacity.
    <code>FF</code> is fully opaque, <code>00</code> is fully transparent.
  </p>
  <PixCode code={`#e84a0080   // orange at 50% opacity
#e8ddd040   // beige at 25% opacity
#FFFFFF00   // fully transparent white`} />

  <h2>Color block</h2>
  <p>
    A <code>color</code> block defines named colors that can be reused
    throughout the program. Each entry maps a name to a hex color.
  </p>
  <PixCode code={`color {
    warm: #e84a00
    light: #e8ddd0
    dark: #2a1208
}`} />

  <h2>Referencing named colors</h2>
  <p>
    Use <code>color &lt;name&gt;</code> wherever a color value is expected.
  </p>
  <PixCode code={`draw x = 3 and y = 5 with color warm
pixel (10, 10) with color dark
circle (8, 8) radius 4 with color light`} />

  <h2>Validation</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Referencing an undefined color name produces an error.</li>
    <li>Color names are case-sensitive.</li>
    <li>An empty <code>color</code> block is allowed.</li>
  </ul>
</Layout>
